Trying this recipe : http://www.thatwhichnourishes.com/the-mac-and-cheese/



450 pasta

112g butter (1/2 cup butter)
1/2 cup flour (120g)
4 cups milk = 1 litre
6 cups cheddar + gouda 680g ( I used 400g cheddar and 290 gouda)
	I think 600g is ok (600g cheddar mature)
1/2 tbl salt
1/2 tbl pepper
2 tbl butter = 28g
1/2 cup panko bread crumbs

per batch cooked in the oven : 
	2 tbl butter = 28g
	1/2 cup panko bread crumbs
	15+min at 180 per batch

pasta : used serpentini : 1 teaspoon salt al dente

Notes :
	chapellure mni tbda tb9b9 7bs otherwise its too thick. No leave it thick so the mac doesn't cook more
	if you want to use plat ceramique cook the pasta less. : cook it 2 minutes less

Four :
	180c for 25 minutes until you smell it cooked.
	
